Rating: 4
I have made this recipe 4 or 5 times now, and absolutly love it! Its always a hit with whoever I am cooking for. I have used a couple different beers, but New Castle really gives it the best taste, over darker and hoppier beers. I also have used Chinese Five spice instead of all spice and think it tastes much better. I serve this over roasted garlic mashed potatoes and its the perfect combination and the thinner sauce isn't a problem on mashed potatoes as it might be over noodles. The roasted garlic potatoes really brings the chicken up a notch. I also used just a bit more mustard and definitely switch out the Vinegar with balsamic and sometimes I need to add flour and sometimes I don't. I highly reccomend this dish and its pretty easy to make too! If you have tried it and didn't like it, maybe try switching up the beer you used, it really affects the flavor.

