Rating: 3
This is definitely one of my new favorite easy meals!! If you like carmelized balsamic onions, you'll love this dish (if you switch out the red wine vinegar with balsamic, that is). I followed the recipe closely, but did take the advice of previous reviewers by adding 1 Tbsp flour to the onion mixture (after it cooked 10 min), and then I also added probably about 2 Tbsp balsamic vinegar to the onions and stirred till it thickened up. Then I added the bay leaves, mustard (I increased it to 3 tsp), sugar, broth, and beer. I mixed this all together and then added the chicken. I will do exactly the same next time, as we thought it was perfect. I used a Black Butte Porter, and the flavor was great--not bitter at all, and we could really taste the beer. We had it with noodles as suggested, and I thought they went well together, as there was a lot of yummy sauce to be soaked up! We will definitely make again.

